LAGOS  – Dr. Chidia Maduekwe, a gov­ernorship aspirant for Abia State under the All Progres­sives Congress (APC), has assured Abia residents that if elected as the state’s chief executive, he would rescue the state from the plague of the deplorable and ailing economy. Maduekwe, the Managing Director/CEO of Nigerian Film Corporation, made the pledge when he hosted jour­nalists during a media brief­ing in Abuja on Wednesday. The politician said: “Our present situation in Abia State demands immediate response. There is no room for margin of error or for trial and error. The principles of fresh esoter­ic management theories have no place in the present gover­nance needs of Abia. Adebomehin Appointed As Substantive SGoF DELTA: Police Nab 25 Cultists, Burst Drug Cartel “The solution lies with known and workable princi­ples that can guarantee the urgent emancipation and migration of Abia people who are currently locked up within the enclave of decrepit deplorable despondency into self-assured dependency born out of certainty embedded or encapsulated within the sin­gle affirmative and assertive­ness in the principles of Nkaa G’eme!.